Reasoning: 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is the most likely category as the paper presents a simulation program for a multi-agent system in urban traffic networks.
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the program employs a Model Predictive Controller to avoid collisions.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper discusses control strategies for urban traffic networks.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the program uses a Consensus-Based Auction Algorithm Modified to determine crossing priorities at intersections.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as the program uses a learning algorithm to determine crossing priorities.
